{"url": 0, "date": 0, "text": "98 The tribe of the  Swedes  ( Suiones ) is first mentioned by  Tacitus  in his  Germania ."}
{"url": 1, "date": 1, "text": "100 The Iron Age settlement at  Upp\u00e5kra  is founded."}
{"url": 2, "date": 2, "text": "530 The possibly legendary  Battle on the Ice of Lake V\u00e4nern  is supposed to have taken place."}
{"url": 3, "date": 3, "text": "750-790 The trade center  Birka  is established on  Lake M\u00e4laren , near present-day  Stockholm ."}
{"url": 4, "date": 4, "text": "800 The  R\u00f6k Runestone  is carved."}
{"url": 5, "date": 5, "text": "829 The monk  Ansgar  makes the first campaign to introduce  Christianity  to Sweden."}
{"url": 6, "date": 6, "text": "960 Birka  is abandoned."}
{"url": 7, "date": 7, "text": "980 The  city of Sigtuna  is founded."}
{"url": 8, "date": 8, "text": "990 The  city of Lund  is founded."}
{"url": 9, "date": 9, "text": "984 The  Battle of F\u00fdrisvellir  takes place near  Uppsala ."}
{"url": 10, "date": 10, "text": "1000 Gothi   \u00deorgeirr Lj\u00f3svetningago\u00f0i  endorses the adoption of  Christianity ."}
{"url": 11, "date": 11, "text": "1004 King  Olof Sk\u00f6tkonung  is baptized and makes  Christianity  the official religion of Sweden."}
{"url": 12, "date": 12, "text": "1036 Ingvar the Far-Travelled  leads an unsuccessful viking attack against  Persia ."}
{"url": 13, "date": 13, "text": "1085 The  city of Helsingborg  is founded."}
{"url": 14, "date": 14, "text": "1087 The  Temple at Uppsala , the central place of worship within  Ancient Norse paganism , is destroyed at the order of King  Inge the Elder ."}
{"url": 15, "date": 15, "text": "1187 Estonians invade and burn down  Sigtuna ."}
{"url": 16, "date": 16, "text": "The  city of Nyk\u00f6ping  is founded."}
{"url": 17, "date": 17, "text": "1208 The  Battle of Lena  takes place."}
{"url": 18, "date": 18, "text": "1240 The  Battle of the Neva  takes place."}
{"url": 19, "date": 19, "text": "1252 The  city of Stockholm  is founded."}
{"url": 20, "date": 20, "text": "1280 The  Ordinance of Alsn\u00f6  gives birth to the  fr\u00e4lse , a class of tax-exempt secular nobility, in Sweden."}
{"url": 21, "date": 21, "text": "1306 The conflict known as the  H\u00e5tuna games  takes place."}
{"url": 22, "date": 22, "text": "1310 The  Treaty of Helsingborg  is signed, establishing peace between Sweden, Norway and Denmark."}
{"url": 23, "date": 23, "text": "1317 The  Nyk\u00f6ping Banquet  takes place, following which  King Birger  imprisons his two brothers and starves them to death."}
{"url": 24, "date": 24, "text": "1319 Sweden and  Norway  are first united."}
{"url": 25, "date": 25, "text": "1323 The  Treaty of N\u00f6teborg  is signed, establishing peace between Sweden and the  Novgorod Republic ."}
{"url": 26, "date": 26, "text": "1344 The  Bridgettine Order  is founded by  St. Bridget ( Heliga Birgitta ) ."}
{"url": 27, "date": 27, "text": "1350 The  Black Death  arrives in Sweden."}
{"url": 28, "date": 28, "text": "1359 King  Magnus IV of Sweden  summons the first Swedish  Riksdag ."}
{"url": 29, "date": 29, "text": "1389 February 24 The  Battle of \u00c5sle  takes place."}
{"url": 30, "date": 30, "text": "1397 Sweden, Denmark and Norway unite into the  Kalmar Union ."}
{"url": 31, "date": 31, "text": "1398 Gotland  is conquered by  Teutonic Knights ."}
{"url": 32, "date": 32, "text": "1409 The  Teutonic Order  sells Gotland to the Kalmar Union."}
{"url": 33, "date": 33, "text": "1434 The  Engelbrekt rebellion , led by  Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson  against King  Erik of Pomerania , begins."}
{"url": 34, "date": 34, "text": "1436 Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson is assassinated."}
{"url": 35, "date": 35, "text": "1471 The  Battle of Brunkeberg  takes place."}
{"url": 36, "date": 36, "text": "1477 Uppsala University  is founded."}
{"url": 37, "date": 37, "text": "1495 The  Russo-Swedish War (1495-1497)  begins."}
{"url": 38, "date": 38, "text": "1497 The Russo-Swedish War ends."}
{"url": 39, "date": 39, "text": "1520 The  Stockholm bloodbath  occurs at the order of  Christian II of Denmark ."}
{"url": 40, "date": 40, "text": "1523 Gustav Vasa  liberates Stockholm, reasserting Sweden's independence from Denmark-Norway and initiating the monarchical rule of the  House of Vasa ."}
{"url": 41, "date": 41, "text": "1524 The  Treaty of Malm\u00f6  is signed. Denmark-Norway recognizes the independence of Sweden, while in return Sweden renounces its claims to  Scania  and  Blekinge ."}
{"url": 42, "date": 42, "text": "1526 The first Swedish translation of the New Testament is published."}
{"url": 43, "date": 43, "text": "1529 The  Westrogothian Rebellion  takes place."}
{"url": 44, "date": 44, "text": "1531 The  Third Dalecarlian Rebellion , also knows as the Bell Rebellion ( Klockupproret ) begins, and is suppressed two years later."}
{"url": 45, "date": 45, "text": "1535 War with  L\u00fcbeck  leads to the expulsion of the  Hanseatic traders , who previously had a monopoly on foreign trade."}
{"url": 46, "date": 46, "text": "1540 The first full Swedish translation of the Bible, the  Gustav Vasa Bible , is published."}
{"url": 47, "date": 47, "text": "1542 Nils Dacke  starts a  peasant uprising  in  Sm\u00e5land , which is defeated the following year."}
{"url": 48, "date": 48, "text": "1554 Border skirmishes between Sweden and Russia lead to the outbreak of the  Russo-Swedish War (1554-1557) ."}
{"url": 49, "date": 49, "text": "1555 A Description of the Northern Peoples (Historia de Gentibus Septentrionalibus)  by  Olaus Magnus  is published."}
{"url": 50, "date": 50, "text": "1561 Estonia  becomes a  Swedish dominion ."}
{"url": 51, "date": 51, "text": "1567 The  Sture Murders  take place at the order of King  Eric XIV ."}
{"url": 52, "date": 52, "text": "1577 February 26 Eric XIV dies in imprisonment, most likely murdered."}
{"url": 53, "date": 53, "text": "1584 The  city of Karlstad  is founded."}
{"url": 54, "date": 54, "text": "1592 Poland  and Sweden enter into a short-lived  personal union  following the crowning of  Sigismund III Vasa  as King of Sweden."}
{"url": 55, "date": 55, "text": "1598 A conflict between Duke Charles, later King  Charles IX , and  Sigismund , King of Sweden and Poland, leads to the outbreak of the  War against Sigismund ."}
{"url": 56, "date": 56, "text": "September 25 The  Battle of St\u00e5ngebro  takes place."}
{"url": 57, "date": 57, "text": "1599 The  War against Sigismund  ends, resulting in the deposition of King Sigismund."}
{"url": 58, "date": 58, "text": "1600 March 20 The  Link\u00f6ping Bloodbath  takes place."}
{"url": 59, "date": 59, "text": "1610 The  Ingrian War  between Russia and Sweden begins."}
{"url": 60, "date": 60, "text": "1611 Denmark declares war on Sweden, initiating the  Kalmar War ."}
{"url": 61, "date": 61, "text": "1613 The  Treaty of Kn\u00e4red  is signed, ending the Kalmar War. Sweden is obligated to pay a ransom of one million  thaler  for the return of the fortress of  \u00c4lvsborg ."}
{"url": 62, "date": 62, "text": "1614 The  city of Kristianstad  is founded."}
{"url": 63, "date": 63, "text": "1617 February 27 The  Treaty of Stolbovo  is signed, ending the Ingrian War. Russia cedes the province and fortress of  Kexholm , southwestern  Karelia  and the province of  Ingria  to Sweden, laying the foundation for Sweden's  rise as a Great Power ."}
{"url": 64, "date": 64, "text": "1621 The  city of Gothenburg  is founded."}
{"url": 65, "date": 65, "text": "1628 August 10 The sinking of the Swedish warship  Vasa ."}
{"url": 66, "date": 66, "text": "1630 Sweden enters the  Thirty Years' War ."}
{"url": 67, "date": 67, "text": "1631 April 13 The  Battle of Frankfurt an der Oder  takes place."}
{"url": 68, "date": 68, "text": "September 7 The  Battle of Breitenfeld  takes place."}
{"url": 69, "date": 69, "text": "1632 November 6 The  Battle of L\u00fctzen  takes place. King  Gustav II Adolf  is killed in battle."}
{"url": 70, "date": 70, "text": "1638 The colony of  New Sweden  is established along the Delaware River in North America."}
{"url": 71, "date": 71, "text": "1648 The  Thirty Years' War  ends, with Sweden among the winners. The  Peace of Westphalia  grants Sweden the provinces of  Western Pomerania ,  Wismar , and the bishoprics of  Bremen-Verden ."}
{"url": 72, "date": 72, "text": "1650 The colony of  the Swedish Gold Coast  is established on the  Gulf of Guinea  in present-day  Ghana ."}
{"url": 73, "date": 73, "text": "1654 Queen  Christina  abdicates her throne and converts to  Roman Catholicism , creating a major scandal."}
{"url": 74, "date": 74, "text": "1658 February 26 Treaty of Roskilde .  Denmark-Norway  cedes the provinces of  Blekinge ,  Bornholm ,  Bohusl\u00e4n ,  Scania ,  Tr\u00f8ndelag  and  Halland  to Sweden."}
{"url": 75, "date": 75, "text": "1663 The colony of the Swedish Gold Coast is seized by Denmark, and integrated in  the Danish Gold Coast ."}
{"url": 76, "date": 76, "text": "1666 Lund University  is founded."}
{"url": 77, "date": 77, "text": "1668 The  Swedish National Bank ( Sveriges Riksbank )  is founded."}
{"url": 78, "date": 78, "text": "1674 December 24 Sweden invades  Brandenburg , triggering the  Swedish-Brandenburg War ."}
{"url": 79, "date": 79, "text": "1675 Denmark invades Scania, triggering the  Scanian War ."}
{"url": 80, "date": 80, "text": "1676 June 1 The  Battle of \u00d6land  takes place."}
{"url": 81, "date": 81, "text": "August 17 The  Battle of Halmstad  takes place."}
{"url": 82, "date": 82, "text": "December 4 The  Battle of Lund  takes place."}
{"url": 83, "date": 83, "text": "1677 June 26 The  Siege of Malm\u00f6  takes place."}
{"url": 84, "date": 84, "text": "July 14 The  Battle of Landskrona  takes place."}
{"url": 85, "date": 85, "text": "1678 The  Invasion of R\u00fcgen  takes place."}
{"url": 86, "date": 86, "text": "1679 August 23 The  Treaty of Fontainebleau  is signed, restoring all Danish conquests during the Scanian War to Sweden."}
{"url": 87, "date": 87, "text": "1680 The  city of Karlskrona  is founded."}
{"url": 88, "date": 88, "text": "The  Great Reduction of 1680  is enacted, returning to the  Swedish Crown  lands that had earlier been granted to the nobility."}
{"url": 89, "date": 89, "text": "1697 May 7 The castle of  Tre Kronor  burns down, destroying a significant portion of Sweden's national library and royal archives."}
{"url": 90, "date": 90, "text": "1700 An alliance consisting of Denmark-Norway,  Saxony ,  Poland  and  Russia  declares war on Sweden, initiating the  Great Northern War ."}
{"url": 91, "date": 91, "text": "The  Battle of Narva  takes place."}
{"url": 92, "date": 92, "text": "1702 July 8 The  Battle of Klisz\u00f3w  takes place."}
{"url": 93, "date": 93, "text": "1706 October 13 The  Treaty of Altranst\u00e4dt  is signed, following Sweden's victorious invasion of Poland. King  Augustus the Strong  is forced to renounce his claims to the Polish throne and his  alliance with Russia ."}
{"url": 94, "date": 94, "text": "1708 January 1 Charles XII crosses the  Vistula , initiating the  Swedish invasion of Russia ."}
{"url": 95, "date": 95, "text": "1709 June 27 The  Battle of Poltava  takes place. The Swedish army under Charles XII is destroyed by the Russian forces of  Peter the Great , marking the beginning of Sweden's decline as a  Great Power ."}
{"url": 96, "date": 96, "text": "1710 February 28 The  Battle of Helsingborg  takes place. Denmark's last attempt to regain Scania fails."}
{"url": 97, "date": 97, "text": "1713 February 1 The  Skirmish at Bender , a battle to remove Charles XII and the remnants of his army from the  Ottoman Empire , takes place."}
{"url": 98, "date": 98, "text": "1718 November 30 Charles XII is killed at  Frederikshald ."}
{"url": 99, "date": 99, "text": "1719 The  Treaties of Stockholm  are signed, requiring Sweden to cede parts of  Swedish Pomerania  to Prussia and  Bremen-Verden  to Hanover."}
{"url": 100, "date": 100, "text": "1720 The  Treaty of Frederiksborg  is signed, requiring Sweden to cede  Schleswig  to Denmark-Norway."}
{"url": 101, "date": 101, "text": "1721 The  Treaty of Nystad  is signed, requiring Sweden to cede  Estonia ,  Livonia  and  Ingria  to Russia."}
{"url": 102, "date": 102, "text": "1731 The  Swedish East India Company  is founded."}
{"url": 103, "date": 103, "text": "1732 Carl Linnaeus  departs on his  Expedition to Lapland ."}
{"url": 104, "date": 104, "text": "1735 The first edition of  Carl Linnaeus'   Systema Naturae  is published."}
{"url": 105, "date": 105, "text": "1739 June 2 The  Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences  is founded."}
{"url": 106, "date": 106, "text": "1741 August 23 The  Battle of Villmanstrand  takes place."}
{"url": 107, "date": 107, "text": "1742 Anders Celsius  proposes the  Celsius temperature scale ."}
{"url": 108, "date": 108, "text": "1743 The  Fourth Dalecarlian Rebellion  breaks out."}
{"url": 109, "date": 109, "text": "1756 An attempted  coup d'\u00e9tat  by  Queen Louisa Ulrika  and a few devoted nobles to reinstate  absolute monarchy  in Sweden is exposed and subdued."}
{"url": 110, "date": 110, "text": "1757 Sweden enters the  Seven Years' War ."}
{"url": 111, "date": 111, "text": "1762 May 22 The  Treaty of Hamburg  is signed, concluding Sweden's involvement in the Seven Years' War."}
{"url": 112, "date": 112, "text": "1766 The Freedom of the Press Act is enacted, abolishing censorship and restricting limitations only to vocal opposition to the king or the  Church of Sweden ."}
{"url": 113, "date": 113, "text": "1772 Absolute monarchy  is reintroduced in Sweden through the  Revolution of 1772 ."}
{"url": 114, "date": 114, "text": "1773 Carl Wilhelm Scheele  discovers  oxygen ."}
{"url": 115, "date": 115, "text": "The  Royal Swedish Opera  is founded."}
{"url": 116, "date": 116, "text": "1782 Sweden purchases the Caribbean island of  Saint Barth\u00e9lemy  from France."}
{"url": 117, "date": 117, "text": "1786 March 20 The  Swedish Academy  is founded."}
{"url": 118, "date": 118, "text": "1788 Sweden declares war against Russia, beginning the  Russo-Swedish War (1788-90) ."}
{"url": 119, "date": 119, "text": "1790 The  Treaty of V\u00e4r\u00e4l\u00e4  is signed, concluding the Russo-Swedish War."}
{"url": 120, "date": 120, "text": "1792 March 16 King  Gustav III  is assassinated at a masked ball."}
{"url": 121, "date": 121, "text": "1808 The  Finnish War  breaks out."}
{"url": 122, "date": 122, "text": "1809 Sweden cedes  Finland  to Russia following the  Finnish War ."}
{"url": 123, "date": 123, "text": "The  Coup of 1809  is carried out, resulting in the deposition of King  Gustav IV Adolf ."}
{"url": 124, "date": 124, "text": "1810 Karolinska Institutet  is founded."}
{"url": 125, "date": 125, "text": "1814 The countries of Sweden and Norway are  united ."}
{"url": 126, "date": 126, "text": "1832 The  G\u00f6ta Canal , providing a route from  Gothenburg  on the west coast to  S\u00f6derk\u00f6ping  on the east coast, is completed."}
{"url": 127, "date": 127, "text": "1848 The series of riots known as  Marsoroligheterna  take place in Stockholm."}
{"url": 128, "date": 128, "text": "1855 Construction of the first railway line in Sweden begins."}
{"url": 129, "date": 129, "text": "1864 The daily newspaper  Dagens Nyheter  is founded."}
{"url": 130, "date": 130, "text": "1867 The telecommunications company  Ericsson  is founded by  Lars Magnus Ericsson ."}
{"url": 131, "date": 131, "text": "Alfred Nobel  invents  dynamite ."}
{"url": 132, "date": 132, "text": "1873 Sweden and Denmark form the  Scandinavian Monetary Union ."}
{"url": 133, "date": 133, "text": "The  krona  replaces the  riksdaler  as the currency of Sweden."}
{"url": 134, "date": 134, "text": "1876 The office of  prime minister ( statsminister )  is instituted."}
{"url": 135, "date": 135, "text": "1878 The island of Saint Barth\u00e9lemy is sold back to France."}
{"url": 136, "date": 136, "text": "1884 The daily newspaper  Svenska Dagbladet  is founded."}
{"url": 137, "date": 137, "text": "The  Fredrika Bremer Association , Sweden's oldest women's rights organization, is founded."}
{"url": 138, "date": 138, "text": "1889 The  Social Democratic Party  is founded."}
{"url": 139, "date": 139, "text": "1897 S. A. Andr\u00e9e 's arctic balloon  expedition ."}
{"url": 140, "date": 140, "text": "1901 The first  Nobel Prizes  are awarded."}
{"url": 141, "date": 141, "text": "1904 The  Moderate Party ( Moderaterna )  is founded."}
{"url": 142, "date": 142, "text": "1905 The  personal union  between Sweden and Norway is  dissolved ."}
{"url": 143, "date": 143, "text": "1906 An official  spelling reform  of the Swedish language is enacted, reforming and simplifying the previous spelling."}
{"url": 144, "date": 144, "text": "1909 The  Stockholm School of Economics ( Handelsh\u00f6gskolan i Stockholm )  is founded."}
{"url": 145, "date": 145, "text": "1919 AB Svensk Filmindustri  is founded."}
{"url": 146, "date": 146, "text": "1921 June 30 Capital punishment is abolished for all crimes committed in peacetime."}
{"url": 147, "date": 147, "text": "1934 Crisis in the Population Question  ( Kris i befolkningsfr\u00e5gan )  by  Alva  and  Gunnar Myrdal  is published, and plays a major role in the design of Sweden's welfare policy."}
{"url": 148, "date": 148, "text": "1938 The  Saltsj\u00f6baden Agreement , establishing rules for  collective bargaining  and trade relations, is signed."}
{"url": 149, "date": 149, "text": "1943 The food packaging company  Tetra Pak  is founded by  Ruben Rausing ."}
{"url": 150, "date": 150, "text": "1945 January 17 Raoul Wallenberg  is detained by Soviet authorities in  Budapest  and subsequently disappears."}
{"url": 151, "date": 151, "text": "1947 The furniture company  IKEA  is founded by  Ingvar Kamprad ."}
{"url": 152, "date": 152, "text": "1954 October 29 Sweden conducts its first television broadcast."}
{"url": 153, "date": 153, "text": "1967 September 3 Right-hand traffic  is introduced in Sweden."}
{"url": 154, "date": 154, "text": "1971 The  Riksdag  becomes  unicameral ."}
{"url": 155, "date": 155, "text": "1973 The Norrmalmstorg  bank robbery and hostage crisis  takes place."}
{"url": 156, "date": 156, "text": "1986 February 28 Prime Minister and Social Democratic leader  Olof Palme  is murdered."}
{"url": 157, "date": 157, "text": "1994 The  MS Estonia disaster  occurs en route from Tallinn to Stockholm. 852 people on board are killed."}
{"url": 158, "date": 158, "text": "1995 Sweden becomes a member of the  European Union ."}
{"url": 159, "date": 159, "text": "1999 The  Church of Sweden  is separated from the state and becomes an independent organization."}
{"url": 160, "date": 160, "text": "2000 July 1 The  \u00d8resund Bridge  is opened, creating a road and railway connection between Sweden and mainland Europe."}
{"url": 161, "date": 161, "text": "2003 Voters decide not to adopt the  Euro  as the country's official currency."}
{"url": 162, "date": 162, "text": "2009 May 1 Same-sex marriage is  legalized  in Sweden."}
